column5: Does anyone know if there is a public boat launch on Lake Eugenia? Heard it has some good bass fishing.
Yes, it's just East of 'town', but you have to pay on weekends.
$17.00 I Believe, they really don't want tourist dollars to be spent in the area & no seasons pass if your not a local resident Tight Lines SBK
Bass fishing has taken a big hit there in recent years... Not as good as it used to be.

Thanks for the information guys, thinking of going up for a day instead of Simcoe. Staff was there at an uncle's cottage and caught two six pounders. Looks like a nice little lake. Can't blame them for wanting to keep it to themselves. Looks like a lot of cottages on the lake. google Earth shows some nice spots . What are the rivers coming out of it? Looks fairly large.  Bill
